This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm for aggregating trust in peer-to-peer networks. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as it aims to mitigate attacks by malicious peers. Additionally, it could be categorized under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with reputation systems in peer-to-peer networks. The Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories are also possible as the paper discusses the convergence and efficiency of the proposed algorithm.
